The installation is complete. You can start the program by clicking on the script named "Settings.sh" on the desktop.

If clicking the script doesn't open it, you can open a terminal on the desktop and enter the following command:

1 - bash Settings.sh

Source files location: ~/USM-S

Note: Opacity adjustment is specifically applied to the XFCE4 system and may not work in different desktop environments.

Note: After reading this, you can delete this file and the installation folder you downloaded.